        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-8">
                <h2>What you’ll learn on this course</h2>
                <div class="tl-subjects--accordion">
                    <button class="tl-subjects--accordion--button"><span>Core content</span></button>
                    <div class="tl-subjects--accordion--panel">
                        <p>
                            Students will develop an understanding of a broad range of issues relevant to the sector, including:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="tl-list--bullet">
                            <li>sustainability, including environmental legislation, sustainable development, climate change and waste management principles</li>
                            <li>the principles of biosecurity</li>
                            <li>employment rights and responsibilities and progression opportunities within the sector</li>
                            <li>ethical principles</li>
                            <li>the supply chain and principles of stock management</li>
                            <li>business organisations, enterprise skills and project management</li>
                            <li>characteristics protected by equality legislation</li>
                            <li>communication</li>
                            <li>principles of customer care</li>
                            <li>finance</li>
                            <li>health and safety </li>
                            <li>information and data</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="tl-subjects--accordion">
                    <button class="tl-subjects--accordion--button"><span>Options to specialise</span></button>
                    <div class="tl-subjects--accordion--panel">
